CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 28, 1950, pg. 2 reads: "Preparing For Carver - Under the leadership of Mrs. Alma Illery, sponsor, the Carver Anniversary Committee met last week in Administration Building of the Board of Education to work up plans for he annual observance of "Carver Week," held each January to perpetuate the memory of Dr. George Washington Carver, agricultural chemist. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait men and women of the Carver Anniversary Committee, including smiling Alma Illery wearing corsage and feathered hat, seated in interior of the Administration Building of the Board of Education with checkered floor and floral curtains
